<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="227" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Remarks</emphasis>
. Of the specimens examined, from Beaufort West (
<figureCitation box="[898,990,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<date box="[952,990,260,285]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" value="2015-01">15i</date>
</figureCitation>
), Rust en Vrede near Oudtshoorn (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[151,194,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" unit="g" value="15.0">15g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and Willowmore (
<figureCitation box="[414,512,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
), all were dissected previously, so the original position of the aedeagus within the genital capsule is unknown. Apices of the aedeagal paraphysis are broken off in the Beaufort West specimen and the Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn specimen has the subgenital plate dismembered. The colour pattern of the crown of the 
<typeStatus box="[196,294,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[312,411,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[368,411,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" unit="g" value="15.0">15g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and Beaufort West specimen (
<figureCitation box="[780,872,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<date box="[836,872,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" value="2015-01">15i</date>
</figureCitation>
) is lighter and in the Oudtshoorn specimen it is darker (
<figureCitation box="[237,335,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
). Styles with a medial digitate process are also found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[958,1122,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracaenus">
<emphasis box="[958,1122,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">D. tetracaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1135,1436,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1436,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Discolopeus thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar style, but without the median digitate process. All other species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1128,1266,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[1128,1266,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have digitate, compressed or depressed style apophyses, with serrate ventral margins and sometimes a single larger apical or ventral tooth. The point distribution map of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[644,796,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triacaenus">
<emphasis box="[644,796,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">D. triacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<figureCitation box="[858,953,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
